the british agreed not to interfere in bhutanese internal affairs and bhutan allowed britain to direct its foreign affairs. this role was assumed by independent india after 1947. two years later, a formal indo-bhutanese accord returned the areas of bhutan annexed by the british, formalized the annual subsidies the country received, and defined india's responsibilities in defense and foreign relations. in december 2006, king jigme singye wangchuck transferred power to his oldest son, the crown prince jigme khesar namgyel wangchuck, bestowing upon him the title of the fifth druk gyalpo. the official coronation took place in november 2008. the fifth 